14:02.900 --> 14:10.000
When the reality is you're going to require a lot more time to develop than you probably think it will require.

14:10.000 --> 14:17.000
One of the things that happens when I have students come under my tutelage is they have been fooled by listening to people

14:17.000 --> 14:21.700
talk about the left side of the chart all the time and they can't execute on the right side.

14:21.700 --> 14:27.600
And it is useful in the beginning, but if that's all there ever is,

14:27.600 --> 14:32.260
and if your educator can't trade on the hard right edge of the chart,

14:32.260 --> 14:37.220
it kind of makes you feel...

14:37.220 --> 14:45.560
well, either a false sense of security or a false sense of confidence that quickly gets evaporated when you trade with a live account

14:45.560 --> 14:49.420
or creates analysis paralysis.

14:49.420 --> 14:56.220
And I have a large body of students that are lumped into one of those categories.

14:56.220 --> 15:05.180
They've been utilizing some other concept or approach or they call it SMC, Smart Money Concepts,

15:05.180 --> 15:09.520
and they'll think to themselves that, you know, this is what's going to have to happen in the chart.

15:09.520 --> 15:13.080
And it isn't because they are lacking narrative.

15:13.080 --> 15:21.780
So one of the things that I'm teaching in this mentorship and my paid mentorship is how to view the marketplace from a narrative standpoint.

15:21.780 --> 15:24.680
What's the logic? Why should the market do what it's doing?

15:24.680 --> 15:29.540
